{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"090250c9-5862-4210-a7f5-7e3ec8a42749","content":"Exit code **8** in Microsoft.Testing.Platform means **\"zero tests discovered.\"** VSTest silently returned 0 in that case, but the new platform intentionally treats it as an error.\n\nThe fix is a single MSBuild property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_yH8j8qE1GsH6r3ztfMY6bl","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing zero-tests exit code"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_3vWC90hSm1TFRUShyE0ZdY","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-5d11afc796674c6696583e0586d2b61b/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n    <!-- Return exit code 0 (not 8) when no tests are discovered, matching VSTest behavior. -->\n    <TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>false</TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-5d11afc796674c6696583e0586d2b61b/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"eba1b1e2-76b4-49d1-bee4-83f8ff668039","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. With Microsoft.Testing.Platform (enabled by `EnableMSTestRunner`), exit code 8 means \"no tests were found.\" When `INCLUDE_SLOW_TESTS` is not defined, all tests are compiled out, resulting in zero tests, which causes exit code 8.\n\nThe fix is to set the MSBuild property `<TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>false</TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>` in the project file (or Directory.Build.props). This tells the platform to return exit code 0 instead of 8 when no tests are discovered.","outputTokens":521,"requestId":"E842:15FC40:2756EBA:29CFF1A:6A049413"},"id":"926b2539-a1e8-44cb-9ac7-e8167f77edd4","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:09:17.570Z","parentId":